                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C114/445h</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Grew</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-11-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1926</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Colombian Minister called and said that he wished to advise me informally
                    that the American note regarding the adherence on the part of the United States
                    to the Protocol of Signature of the Statute for the Permanent Court of
                    International Justice has been submitted by the Colombian Government to the
                    Colombian Congress which has not yet acted upon it. The Minister said that this
                    fact would shortly be communicated to us in a formal note.<note n="33"
                        xml:id="d27fn33">No further communication appears to have been received from
                        the Colombian Government.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J[<hi rend="smallcaps">oseph</hi>] C. G[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >rew</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
